cs.DS, cs.CC, cs.DM, cs.SI, cs.AL

Reasoning: 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a likely category as the paper proposes algorithms to compute single-arm-gapped palindromes based on suffix arrays and suffix trees.
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is also a likely category as the paper discusses the efficiency of the proposed algorithms and their time complexity.
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is a possible category as the paper deals with the classification and properties of a new type of approximate palindrome.
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is a possible category as the paper mentions using the proposed algorithms for analyzing DNA sequences, which can be modeled as networks.
- cs.AL (Automata and Formal Languages) is a possible category as the paper deals with the properties and computation of a new type of palindrome.
